Rating: 3
Good Recipe but even better after I changed a few things. I prefer more of "fry." Added 1 TBS Soy Sauce to ingredient list. Cook at 350 for 45 to 50 minutes, flipping once so both sides of wedges are browned. Potatoes turn into crispy fries. Great served with Ketchup up with you favorite hot sauce.

Rating: 3
A great starter recipe. I add lots of paprika and chile powder, maybe even some cumin, for a great spice rub and gorgeous color. I roast it at 400 for 50 minutes or so, and get GREAT caramelization. The outside is nice and chewy, and the inside is, as my client described, "like a souffle". I didn't like sweet potatoes much until I started treating them this way!

