Rating: 3
I increased the amount of oil to 1 tbs and brushed it on for complete coating (helping eliminate the dryness issue). Mixing all the spices together first makes it easier to sprinkle them on rather than doing it 1/8 tsp. at a time. Temperature-wise, 500 was fine, but I baked them on the middle rack, not the bottom. My boyfriend and I thought the amount of heat from the cayenne was just right.

